    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Before this change, UiState was merging the indexIds directly with the other state,\r\n\r\nNot sure to understand the meaning of the comment. Could you explain? The current format of `uiState` is already the one described by @francoischalifour. I don't think we have to update its structure. The types inside the codebase are not up-to-date though, this is the idea:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\ntype UiState = {\r\n  [indexId: string]: IndexUiState;\r\n};\r\n\r\nconst movies: IndexUiState = {\r\n  query: \"hammer\"\r\n};\r\n\r\nconst songs: IndexUiState = {\r\n  query: \"burning\"\r\n};\r\n\r\nconst uiState: UiState = {\r\n  songs,\r\n  movies\r\n};\r\n```",
